Franklin County Public Health
August 26 at 10:55 AM ·

There's free COVID-19 testing happening this Friday (08/28) and Saturday (08/29)!

If you need to be tested, you can head to the Africentric Center (3223 Allegheny Ave., 43209). Hours are 10 a.m. - 7 p.m. on Friday and 8 a.m. - 8 p.m. on Saturday.

These testing events are open to the public and available to anyone in the community (adults and children), but strictly for those who are uninsured or on medicare or medicaid.

PBLMatters
August 23 at 7:21 AM ·

🎥 Video #8 in our Teacher Toolbox is here!
Featured speaker is Cassie, a middle school math teacher who provides us insights into going virtual with PBL - the good 😃 the bad 😭 and the ugly 🥴!
Cassie was recently honored with the George B. Chapman Teacher Award for Excellence in Mathematics Education from the Martha Holden Jennings Foundation. Way to go!! 🏆

ELeducation
Graham Elementary and Middle School

post_text:
GEMS families,

Today is Sunday, March 8, 2020. I hope you have all been able to enjoy the sun this afternoon! Tomorrow is the start of our final trimester and we have 5 weeks until Spring Break!

Please remember that Thursday afternoon we will be hosting our K-4 Trimester 2 awards ceremony from 2:30 - 3:15pm. Also on Thursday, in the evening will be our 5th - 8th grade celebration of learning. Starting at 6pm, we hope that every family with students in the middle school can attend and help us engage all of the hard work that our students have put in this trimester.

On Friday, our 7th graders will be eating with a few police officers from the Columbus Police Department as part of their Trimester 2 expedition experience.

Have a great evening!

Check out the Linden LEAP!
The LEAP is free to all passengers 12 years old and up. The two shuttles servicing the route will pick up passengers every 12 minutes. It will take 24 minutes to ride from the first to the last stop. The shuttle operate 7 days a week from 6AM-8PM, except for 9:30AM-10:30AM and 3PM-4:30PM Monday-Friday during school release times per federal mandate. The shuttles can accommodate strollers and wheelchairs and can carry up to 12 passengers.

post_text:
This week ahead we are hosting the Scholastic Book Fair at GEMS! Your student will have the opportunity to check it out at various scheduled times throughout the week.

On Wednesday evening, the Kindergarten - 4th grades will have their Celebration of Learning from 6:00pm - 7:30pm. On Thursday evening, the 5th - 8th grades will have their Celebration of Learning from 6:00pm - 7:30pm. We hope you all can come honor the work of our students from Trimester 1.

The book fair will also be open during these evening events. There will also be a resource fair during the Celebration of Learning that will have food items, coats, and pajamas you can browse and take home. If you are interested to volunteer at the resource fair, please contact the school office.

The GEMS annual pajama drive is in full swing! The class or crew that brings in the most pajamas will earn hot chocolate and cookies!

Stay warm and have a great week!

GEMS loves books! Our Scholastic Book Fair opens tomorrow! ⁣
⁣
Students will get a chance to visit Monday-Thursday. Your student may bring cash or you can load their e-wallet (our favorite payment method!). ⁣E-wallets can be loaded from our homepage: https://www.scholastic.com/bf/gemsk8
⁣
Family members are invited to shop during Celebrations of Learning on Wednesday & Thursday at 6pm, or stop by on Friday. ⁣
⁣
#gemscolumbus #wearegems #scholasticbookfair #readeveryday
